The article discusses the field of art therapy and its growing popularity in various countries. It mentions the experiences of Karen Pence, the Second Lady, as she meets with art therapists in different locations. In Egypt, Carol Hammal is the only art therapist and works at a hospital and a holistic treatment center. She conducts workshops to raise awareness about the benefits of art therapy and hopes to train more people in the field. In Israel, there are multiple college and university programs for creative arts therapy, including dance/movement therapy, bibliotherapy, and visual art therapy. Art therapy is offered in schools, for disabled children, cancer patients, and survivors of the Holocaust. The therapists in Israel have developed unique treatment approaches through their work with various populations and are also involved in research. The article concludes by highlighting the benefits of art therapy for healing and expressing gratitude for the dedicated art therapists making a difference in people's lives.